cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper is about using Convolutional Networks for image recognition, localization, and detection. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also introduces a novel deep learning approach to localization, which suggests that it could be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of a single shared network for different tasks, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of Convolutional Networks also suggests that it could be categorized under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper discusses the release of a feature extractor, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia).
